        "title": "OWL API save ontology if reasoner is consistent and changes occurred",
        "body": "<p>I have an ontology that I need to save on file if and only if some changes occured and the reasoner (pellet in my case) is consistent with these changes. So i write:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> reasoner.flush(); //sync reasoner\n if(reasoner.isConsistent())\n manager.saveOntology(ontos[1], new RDFXMLDocumentFormat(), IRI.create((new   File(file)).toURI())); \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I would synchronize Pellet only if the ontology has been modified, than if it is consistent synchronize it and apply changes. Any idea how to proceed?\nThank you<\/p>\n\n<p>(Edit: I use manager.applyChange method in order to modify the ontology).<\/p>\n",
